                            <comment id="85800" author="jlevi" created="Thu, 5 Jun 2014 13:28:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch landed to Master.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="84340" author="sarah" created="Sat, 17 May 2014 04:52:25 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/10360&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/10360&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="84273" author="adilger" created="Fri, 16 May 2014 17:51:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This has failed 10 times in the past two weeks, starting 2014-05-01:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/sub_tests/c712e6b6-d154-11e3-96e1-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://maloo.whamcloud.com/sub_tests/c712e6b6-d154-11e3-96e1-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There doesn&apos;t appear to be an obvious patch that introduced this problem, but at first glance it has something to do with DNE2, maybe being unable to find the files in the striped directories or similar.  It is possible that this is unrelated to DNE2, if there is a delay in precreating objects for the MDT.  It would be useful to run something like &quot;lfs getstripe -R $DIR/$tdir&quot; in case of failure, so that it is possible to see exactly which files were created/found and what the stripe counts are.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sarah, could you please make a patch for that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
